profile_short_name:COL Chiloso WSH v2
profile_designer:Claude
profile_description:Colombia Huila Betania Chiloso Washed COE\vVariety: Chiloso | Altitude: 1800-1900m\vMoisture: 12% (nominal), est. ~10-10.5% (aged 8mo)\vDensity: Unknown (est. 840-870g/L)\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 2 - Maillard extension + development boost\vBased on V1 first roast (log0099) feedback:\v- Cup was flat/bland despite good aroma\v- Maillard phase too fast (106s, ROR 15.4C/min)\v- Dev ratio 16.2% insufficient for aged bean\v\vV2 changes from V1:\v1. roast_profile: replaced F-WSH template 4-point curve\v   with 6-point Catimor V5-style curve for explicit\v   mid-section control. Maillard target 130s (+24s)\v2. expect_fc: 204->200C (actual FC was 197C in log0099)\v3. recommended_level: 2.0->2.5 (target 206C for aged bean)\v4. preheat: 790->810W (V1 mid-section ran slightly cold)\v5. roast_levels adjusted: keep same scale\v\vTarget curve shape:\v  0-210s: drying phase (168C colour change)\v  210-340s: Maillard phase (130s, target ROR ~13.8C/min)\v  340-420s: development (FC->end, ~80s)\v\vExpected results:\v  Maillard: 130s (vs V1 106s)\v  Dev ratio: 18-20% (vs V1 16.2%)\v  Total time: ~400-420s (vs V1 369s)\v  End temp: ~205-206C (vs V1 203.4C)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Light Clean: Level 1.5 (~202C)\v  Light Balanced: Level 2.0 (~204C)\v  Sweet Developed: Level 2.5 (~206C) <- Target\v  Medium Light: Level 3.0 (~208C)\v\vAging note: Level 2.5 selected to compensate for\v8+ months storage. If still flat, try Level 3.0.\v\vC40 pour-over grind: 24-28 clicks\vResting period: 5-7 days minimum\v
